# üõ°Ô∏è Zero to Hero: 365-Day Cybersecurity Roadmap

**Goal:** Transform from a complete beginner to a job-ready Junior Penetration Tester / Security Analyst in 12 months.
**Focus:** Hands-on technical skills, Offensive Security (Red Team), Defensive Basics (Blue Team), and Scripting.
**Motto:** "Try Harder."

---

## üìÖ Quarter 1: The Foundation (Months 1-3)
*Building the bedrock. You cannot hack what you do not understand.*

### üü¢ Month 1: Networking Mastery
The internet is just a giant network. Master how data moves.
- [ ] **Study the OSI Model:** Memorize all 7 layers. Understand data encapsulation.
- [ ] **TCP/IP Protocol Suite:** deeply understand TCP vs UDP, Three-way handshake.
- [ ] **IP Addressing:** Learn IPv4, IPv6, CIDR notation, and Subnetting (Do not skip Subnetting!).
- [ ] **Common Ports & Protocols:** SSH (22), DNS (53), HTTP/S (80/443), SMB (445), RDP (3389).
- [ ] **Lab:** Download **Cisco Packet Tracer** and build a small office network (Router, Switch, PC).
- [ ] **Tool:** Master **Wireshark**. Capture packets on your home network and analyze a TCP handshake.

### üü¢ Month 2: Operating Systems (Linux & Windows)
Hackers live in the terminal.
- [ ] **Virtualization:** Install VirtualBox or VMware. Set up a **Kali Linux** VM and a **Windows 10** VM.
- [ ] **Linux CLI Mastery:**
  - [ ] Navigation (`cd`, `ls`, `pwd`)
  - [ ] File Management (`cp`, `mv`, `rm`, `cat`, `nano/vim`)
  - [ ] Permissions (`chmod`, `chown`, `chgrp`)
  - [ ] Process Management (`ps`, `top`, `kill`)
  - [ ] Text Manipulation (`grep`, `awk`, `sed`, `pipes |`)
- [ ] **Windows Internals:** Understand the Registry, Services, and basic CMD/PowerShell commands.
- [ ] **Resource:** *Linux Basics for Hackers* (Book or equivalent course).

### üü¢ Month 3: Coding & Security Logic
Stop using tools; start building them.
- [ ] **Python for Security:** Learn variables, loops, functions, and libraries (`requests`, `socket`).
- [ ] **Bash Scripting:** Automate simple Linux tasks.
- [ ] **Project:** Write a simple **Port Scanner** in Python (Do not use Nmap, code it yourself using `socket`).
- [ ] **Concepts:** Learn CIA Triad, AAA, Encryption (Symmetric vs Asymmetric), Hashing.

---

## üìÖ Quarter 2: The Art of Attack (Months 4-6)
*Learning how to break systems and find vulnerabilities.*

### üü° Month 4: Web Application Security
The most common attack surface.
- [ ] **OWASP Top 10:** deeply understand the top vulnerabilities (SQLi, XSS, IDOR, Broken Access Control).
- [ ] **HTTP Protocol:** Understand Headers, Cookies, Sessions, GET vs POST.
- [ ] **Tool:** **Burp Suite**. Master the Proxy, Repeater, and Intruder tabs.
- [ ] **Labs:** Complete the Apprentice level labs on **PortSwigger Web Security Academy** (Free).

### üü° Month 5: Network Scanning & Enumeration
Gathering information before the attack.
- [ ] **Nmap:** Master flags (`-sC`, `-sV`, `-p-`, `-O`). Learn NSE (Nmap Scripting Engine).
- [ ] **Vulnerability Assessment:** Understand CVSS scores.
- [ ] **Metasploit Framework:** Learn search, use, set RHOSTS/LHOSTS, exploit, payloads (staged vs stageless).
- [ ] **Brute Forcing:** Learn **Hydra** and **John the Ripper**.
- [ ] **Platform:** Start the "Pre-Security" and "Jr. Penetration Tester" paths on **TryHackMe**.

### üü° Month 6: Privilege Escalation
You are in. Now become God (Root/Admin).
- [ ] **Reverse Shells:** Understand how to catch a shell with Netcat (`nc -lvnp`).
- [ ] **Linux PrivEsc:** SUID binaries, Kernel exploits, Cron jobs. (Tool: **LinPEAS**).
- [ ] **Windows PrivEsc:** Unquoted Service Paths, Token Impersonation. (Tool: **WinPEAS**).
- [ ] **Transferring Files:** Learn how to move files to a victim machine using Python http server, wget, certutil.

---

## üìÖ Quarter 3: Advanced & Corporate Environments (Months 7-9)
*Moving from CTFs to real-world corporate networks.*

### üî¥ Month 7: Active Directory (The Big Boss)
90% of Fortune 500 companies use AD. You must know it.
- [ ] **Architecture:** Domain Controllers, Forests, Trees, Users, Groups, Policies (GPO).
- [ ] **Attacks:** Kerberoasting, AS-REP Roasting, LLMNR Poisoning (Responder), Pass-the-Hash.
- [ ] **Tools:** **BloodHound** (Mapping the AD), **Mimikatz** (Dumping credentials), **Impacket**.
- [ ] **Lab:** Build a Windows Server AD Lab on your machine and hack it.

### üî¥ Month 8: Blue Team Basics & Evasion
Know your enemy (The Defenders).
- [ ] **Logs:** How to read Windows Event Logs and Linux Syslogs.
- [ ] **SIEM:** Understand what Splunk/ELK does.
- [ ] **Firewalls/IDS:** How to evade basic detection (modifying payloads, changing user-agents).
- [ ] **Analysis:** Use VirusTotal and Hybrid Analysis to check malware signatures.

### üî¥ Month 9: Hands-on Intensive (The Grind)
Stop reading, start hacking.
- [ ] **Platform:** **HackTheBox (HTB)**.
- [ ] **Goal:** Root 20 machines (Start with Easy, move to Medium).
- [ ] **Documentation:** Write a detailed "Write-up" for every machine you solve. Save these in a folder; this is your portfolio.

---

## üìÖ Quarter 4: Career & Certification (Months 10-12)
*Proving your skills and getting hired.*

### üîµ Month 10: Certification Prep
Get the HR filter bypass.
- [ ] **Target:** **eJPTv2** (eLearnSecurity Junior Penetration Tester) - Highly recommended for beginners.
- [ ] **Stretch Goal:** **OSCP** (Offensive Security Certified Professional) - The Gold Standard (Hard).
- [ ] **Focus:** Dedicate this month entirely to the course material and labs of your chosen certification.

### üîµ Month 11: Bug Bounty & Real World
- [ ] **Platforms:** Sign up for **HackerOne** or **Bugcrowd**.
- [ ] **Practice:** Look for VDP (Vulnerability Disclosure Programs) that allow safe testing.
- [ ] **Report Writing:** Learn to write professional reports. Impact > Technical Complexity. Explain *why* the bug matters to the business.

### üîµ Month 12: The Job Hunt
- [ ] **GitHub Polish:** clean up your repos, pin your Python tools and CTF write-ups.
- [ ] **LinkedIn:** Optimize profile. Title: "Cybersecurity Researcher" or "Aspiring Penetration Tester". Connect with the community.
- [ ] **Mock Interviews:** Prepare for technical questions (e.g., "Explain the XSS to a 5-year-old," "What happens when you type google.com?").
- [ ] **Apply:** Apply to SOC Analyst L1, Junior Pentester, or IT Security Administrator roles.

---

## üìö Essential Resources

### Platforms
* **TryHackMe:** Best for guided learning.
* **HackTheBox:** Best for unguided practice.
* **PortSwigger Academy:** The Bible of Web Security.

### YouTube Channels
* NetworkChuck
* The Cyber Mentor (TCM)
* IppSec (Watch him solve HTB boxes)
* John Hammond

### Tools to Master
`Nmap`, `Burp Suite`, `Metasploit`, `Wireshark`, `Netcat`, `Gobuster/Dirb`, `Hydra`, `Hashcat`, `BloodHound`.

---

## üèÜ Rules of Success

1.  **Google Dorking:** If you are stuck, search for 15 minutes before asking for help. Google is a skill.
2.  **Take Notes:** Use **Obsidian** or **Notion**. If you don't document it, you didn't learn it.
3.  **Consistency:** 1 hour every day is better than 10 hours on Sunday.
4.  **Ethics:** Never touch a system you do not have permission to test. Jail is not part of the roadmap.

